awards:
[{'title': 'The EFCATS Young Generation Catalysis Challenge - The Second Prize', 'description': 'I was selected to represent Turkey at the first young generation catalysis challenge organized by the European Federation of Catalysis Societies (EFCATS). Two young researchers from each of the 25 EFCATS nations were selected by national committees and invited to attend the exclusive event hosted at Wageningen University and Research (WUR) in the Netherlands from 9th-11th July 2018. Participants were split into multidisciplinary and multinational teams and were tasked to write a research proposal which may contribute to securing the sustainable delivery of food, feed, fuels or materials for our future society as a team. The teams presented their proposals to a board of EFCAT representatives. The top three research proposals were selected and the team members were awarded. My team included participants from Austria, the Czech Republic, Denmark and the United Kingdom and won the second prize for our proposal on the design of novel Pt-based cluster catalysts for selective conversion of glycerol to 1,3-propanediol by in-situ H2 generation.', 'issuer': 'The European Association of Catalysis Societies', 'date': {'month': 7, 'day': None, 'year': 2018}}, {'title': 'GSNAS Dr. Haluk Sanver Doctorate Award', 'description': 'Dr. Haluk Sanver Doctorate Award is given to the thesis work that is selected by the "Selection Committee" among the doctoral studies completed in the previous semester in the Chemical Engineering Department of METU.
